#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.33/guides/aws-lambda-http.adoc
msgid "Tracing with AWS XRay and GraalVM"
msgstr "Rastreabilidade com AWS X-Ray e GraalVM"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.33/guides/aws-lambda-http.adoc
msgid ""
"If you are building native images, and want to use https://aws.amazon.com/xray[AWS X-Ray Tracing] with your lambda\n"
"you will need to include `quarkus-amazon-lambda-xray` as a dependency in your pom.  The AWS X-Ray\n"
"library is not fully compatible with GraalVM, so we had to do some integration work to make this work."
msgstr "Se estiver criando imagens nativas e quiser usar o link:https://aws.amazon.com/xray[AWS X-Ray Tracing] com seu lambda, serĂĄ necessĂĄrio incluir `quarkus-amazon-lambda-xray` como uma dependĂŞncia no seu pom. A biblioteca do AWS X-Ray nĂŁo ĂŠ totalmente compatĂ­vel com o GraalVM, portanto, tivemos que fazer algum trabalho de integraĂ§ĂŁo para que isso funcionasse."

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.33/guides/aws-lambda-http.adoc
msgid "Security Integration"
msgstr "IntegraĂ§ĂŁo da seguranĂ§a"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.33/guides/aws-lambda-http.adoc
msgid ""
"When you invoke an HTTP request on the API Gateway, the Gateway turns that HTTP request into a JSON event document that is\n"
"forwarded to a Quarkus Lambda.  The Quarkus Lambda parses this json and converts in into an internal representation of an HTTP\n"
"request that can be consumed by any HTTP framework Quarkus supports (Jakarta REST, servlet, Reactive Routes)."
msgstr "Quando vocĂŞ realiza uma requisiĂ§ĂŁo HTTP no API Gateway, o Gateway transforma essa requisiĂ§ĂŁo HTTP em um documento de evento JSON que ĂŠ encaminhado para uma Lambda do Quarkus. A Lambda do Quarkus processa esse JSON e o converte em uma representaĂ§ĂŁo interna de uma requisiĂ§ĂŁo HTTP que pode ser consumida por qualquer framework HTTP suportado pelo Quarkus (Jakarta REST, servlet, Reactive Routes)."

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.33/guides/aws-lambda-http.adoc
msgid ""
"API Gateway supports many ways to securely invoke on your HTTP endpoints that are backed by Lambda and Quarkus.\n"
"If you enable it, Quarkus will automatically parse relevant parts of the https://docs.aws.amazon.com/apigateway/latest/developerguide/http-api-develop-integrations-lambda.html[event json document]\n"
"and look for security based metadata and register a `java.security.Principal` internally that can be looked up in Jakarta REST\n"
"by injecting a `jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext`, via `HttpServletRequest.getUserPrincipal()` in servlet, and `RouteContext.user()` in Reactive Routes.\n"
"If you want more security information, the `Principal` object can be typecast to\n"
"a class that will give you more information."
msgstr "O API Gateway suporta diversas maneiras de invocar com seguranĂ§a os endpoints HTTP que sĂŁo baseados em Lambda e Quarkus. Se habilitado, o Quarkus processarĂĄ automaticamente as partes relevantes do https://docs.aws.amazon.com/apigateway/latest/developerguide/http-api-develop-integrations-lambda.html[documento json do evento], buscarĂĄ metadados de seguranĂ§a e registrarĂĄ internamente um `java.security.Principal` que poderĂĄ ser consultado no Jakarta REST injetando um `jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext` , via `HttpServletRequest.getUserPrincipal()` em servlet e `RouteContext.user()` em Reactive Routes. Se desejar mais informaĂ§Ăľes de seguranĂ§a, o objeto `Principal` pode ser convertido em uma classe que fornecerĂĄ mais detalhes adicionais."

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.33/guides/aws-lambda-http.adoc
